snippet.textDisplay: Our defence (which was decent in the early part of the season) has completely fallen apart. 1 incompletion in the entire game! Did anyone even try to stop him? I liked Jacoby when I saw the game against Kansas earlier in the season & thought that it looked promising. You can´t really fault him for his first season, since our O-line was by far the worst in team history, but now there´s no excuses anymore & he just isn´t cutting it. He´s would be a decent back up, but he´s nowhere near good enough to be a starter & probably never will be. It´s time to cut our losses, lose the rest of the games this year on purpose & try to draft a new QB, so that in a few years we might have a chance again, because this is getting embarrassing for every Colts fan to witness. At least in the awful 2-14 season there was an excuse, since they didn´t have a plan B in case Manning couldn´t come back & it backfired on them big time. This is bad on a whole different level.

snippet.textDisplay: See this just illustrates what I always say about Brees, he’s always been a prolific and even gifted passer of the ball, but Brees is always about his stats over winning championships. Why so much passing in this game? Seems like the whole game plan was let’s get Brees his record. Reminds me of that game Michael Strahan got his single season sack record. Records are great, but what’s your franchise record in the postseason. I looked it up, it’s 9-11 overall. Yeah you won this game, but the Colts aren’t a very consistently good team. We’ve seen what happens when better defenses shut Drew down. Congrats Drew, you’re an all time great, as far as numbers, but I don’t see you doing much in the postseason against way better defenses. You’re team is better, Saints fans, when you are a balanced team. That air it out style offense won’t work in the post season...
